  "original_title": "\u0db0\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd2\u0dc1\u0dca \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dd3\u0da7 \u0d87\u0db4",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Dhanish Ali granted bail",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Colombo Chief Magistrate Nandana Amarasinghe today (15) ordered that social activist Dhanish Ali, who was remanded in custody in connection with the alleged forced entry into the television corporation, be released on two sureties of 25000 rupees and 5 lakh rupees each.",
        "According to the Public Property Act related to this incident, the magistrate released the suspect on bail stating that there are not enough facts to keep the suspect in custody.",
        "The magistrate also ordered the suspect to go to the Kuruduwatta police and give a statement regarding this incident.",
        "The suspect was arrested by the police on the 26th while he was waiting in a plane to go abroad.",
        "On the 27th, the Fort Magistrate had ordered to remand the suspect, who was arrested according to a warrant issued by the court, after being brought back to court.",
        "Kurunduwatta police had reported the facts to the court regarding this incident.",
        "31-year-old Dhanish Ali, a resident of Kurunegala Webada area, was released on bail.",
        "Also, four suspects including Dhanish Ali have been remanded until the 26th by the Colombo Fort Magistrate's Court in relation to the alleged incident of trespassing into the Presidential Palace and damaging its property."
      ],
